tip.text: Located beside Naughty Nuri. This bar has no menu and you just need to tick on your preferences and then let the bartender do his job! They will amaze you. The staffs are friendly and helpful!
One thing I really loved their teatime other than their friendly service was the hot savory food that served tgt with the set. 2pax for RM220 and reminder the tea is not refillable(RM30) to refill.
Came here to try out their watermelon cake only but I feel like the cake (Rm15.50 )is just so-so. Oh and they didn't bother to serve me water probably cuz I only ordered A CAKE ONLY.
The pork noodle is Rm9 for a Regular one plus an egg. I definitely prefer this over another because it is less oily, less salty and not so thirsty after eating it. The restaurant is spacious too!

We came in for lunch and we decided to order Tuna cut roll as appetizer and Chirashi Donburi as main course. However, the Tuna wasn't served even until I finished my Donburi. Food: so-so Service: suck
Large Pho for $12 and Small for $10. Portion is generous and the broth is delicious too. Service is good and the price is reasonable.
$12 dollar pho comes with bean spout and basil! The slice beef is tender and broth is delicious. Perfect for a rainy day!
My prawn mee tastes so-so only :( i hope they can put more sweet sauce for the popiah becuz it was totally tasteless
Swerving is fast but the food tastes so so only.
